to go play baseball with them

20:51.684 --> 20:54.553
in the reservoir when it
dried up a couple of years ago.

20:54.555 --> 20:57.322
They ended up tying me to a
fence post with a skipping rope

20:57.324 --> 21:00.327
using me for Spud Gun
target practice.

21:01.327 --> 21:03.394
OK.

21:03.396 --> 21:06.533
Well, then beat them up.

21:38.565 --> 21:41.501
I think we scared them off.

21:43.436 --> 21:45.505
They're gone.

21:48.541 --> 21:52.443
Look, I'll have a word
with Gregory Mathison myself

21:52.445 --> 21:54.814
in the next couple of days.

22:01.454 --> 22:02.789
Anyhow...

22:03.856 --> 22:05.356
We should head back.

22:05.358 --> 22:07.827
No point going any further, Ray.

22:10.931 --> 22:12.363
You all right?

22:12.365 --> 22:13.765
Yeah.

22:13.767 --> 22:16.801
- You look spooked.
- It's nothing.

22:56.042 --> 22:57.944
What the...

24:33.874 --> 24:35.543
Ah, crap!

26:09.970 --> 26:11.038
Uncle Morgan?

26:13.038 --> 26:14.538
Shit!

26:17.576 --> 26:19.145
- What was that light?
- You OK?

26:20.846 --> 26:22.148
Where's your uncle?

26:36.663 --> 26:38.028
Kenneth, come on.

26:38.030 --> 26:41.865
No! No, no, no...

26:41.867 --> 26:45.905
Kenneth! Kenneth, Kenneth!
What's going on?

26:48.040 --> 26:50.941
Morgan!

26:50.943 --> 26:53.611
It's me! It's me!
It's nothing! It's nothing!

26:53.613 --> 26:55.680
- Look at me!
- Billy!

26:55.682 --> 26:58.615
We gotta go! We gotta go!

26:58.617 --> 27:00.617
Come on!

27:00.619 --> 27:02.956
Morgan!

27:04.057 --> 27:06.026
Morgan!

27:07.027 --> 27:09.192
- What's happening?
- Move along.

27:09.194 --> 27:11.898
- what's wrong with him?
- Move!

27:14.768 --> 27:16.100
What's wrong with him?
Billy?

27:16.102 --> 27:18.702
Ray! Come on! Let's go!

27:18.704 --> 27:20.270
Ray!

27:20.272 --> 27:22.907
- You seen Morgan?
- What?

27:22.909 --> 27:26.080
- Morgan, your brother!
- He's not with you?

27:39.025 --> 27:41.228
Dad? What's wrong
with Uncle Kenneth?

28:10.123 --> 28:12.256
What am I doing?

28:14.094 --> 28:17.096
- Open the door!
- Oh, my God.

28:22.035 --> 28:24.369
What's wrong?
Oh, my God!

28:24.371 --> 28:25.803
What's happened?

28:25.805 --> 28:27.671
Honey, is he hurt?

28:27.673 --> 28:29.239
- Are you hurt?
- I don't know.

28:29.241 --> 28:30.908
Honey! Billy!

28:30.910 --> 28:32.075
What's wrong with you?

28:32.077 --> 28:34.112
Oh, my God, he looks terrible,
Billy. What's happened?

28:34.114 --> 28:36.748
- I don't know.
- Where is Morgan?

28:36.750 --> 28:37.981
Honey, speak to me!

28:37.983 --> 28:40.651
- Is Morgan here?
- Isn't he with you?

28:40.653 --> 28:43.187
No, he's, uh...

28:43.189 --> 28:45.757
- Dad!
- Ray!

28:45.759 --> 28:46.857
- Ray!
- Dad!

28:46.859 --> 28:49.826
Ray, what's...
what's going on?

28:49.828 --> 28:53.296
- Ray! Ray! Where is Morgan?
- What's happening?

28:53.298 --> 28:56.133
- I'll go look for him, OK?
- No, we shouldn't go outside.

28:56.135 --> 28:58.702
What are you so afraid of,
Billy?

28:58.704 --> 29:01.205
- Morgan's missing, Ray.
- Missing?

29:01.207 --> 29:03.141
No, no, he's not missing,
he's...

29:03.143 --> 29:05.176
He's probably lost
in the woods somewhere.

29:05.178 --> 29:07.978
- I'm calling the Sheriff.
- He's making his way back now.

29:07.980 --> 29:11.783
- I'm calling the Sheriff.
- Olivia, that's not gonna help!

29:11.785 --> 29:14.451
Olivia, stop!
That's not gonna help!

29:14.453 --> 29:16.187
Can I have the Sheriff, please?

29:16.189 --> 29:19.856
Sheriff? The police are sitting
in our front room right now!

29:19.858 --> 29:21.959
They're not exactly much use,
are they?

29:21.961 --> 29:25.028
- He needs a doctor, Ray.
- OK, look, let's...

29:25.030 --> 29:28.432
Let's just take a level
perspective and calm down, OK?

29:28.434 --> 29:30.468
Take a step back, OK?

29:30.470 --> 29:35.241
That's what too much TV and
not enough fruit does to you.

29:36.843 --> 29:39.443
OK, let's...

29:39.445 --> 29:42.880
You know, your imagination
works over sometimes,

29:42.882 --> 29:47.184
and you start thinking
about things, and...

29:47.186 --> 29:48.119
Look...

29:48.121 --> 29:50.353
Olivia, I'll find Morgan.

29:50.355 --> 29:52.159
I'll be right back.

29:59.298 --> 30:01.167
Morgan?

30:06.405 --> 30:08.142
Morgan!

30:14.380 --> 30:16.316
I don't...

30:22.521 --> 30:24.822
I don't know what I saw.

30:24.824 --> 30:26.125
Morgan?

30:29.394 --> 30:31.996
Goddamn, Morgan.

30:31.998 --> 30:34.234
Come on, buddy.

30:38.805 --> 30:40.470
Morgan!

30:47.279 --> 30:49.316
Something's happening...

31:08.134 --> 31:10.269
Something unnatural.

31:32.558 --> 31:34.293
Something evil.

35:40.672 --> 35:42.408
Ugh!

36:03.128 --> 36:04.498
Noah!

37:06.759 --> 37:10.327
- Is everyone OK?
- What the hell was that?

37:17.670 --> 37:19.739
Billy.

37:27.746 --> 37:30.180
Hey, boy.

37:30.182 --> 37:32.782
What did you see?

37:32.784 --> 37:35.321
What is it, boy?

38:01.847 --> 38:03.817
Ray! Don't!

38:57.836 --> 38:59.672
Noah!

39:01.373 --> 39:03.509
Stay back, son.

39:05.844 --> 39:07.680
Morgan?

39:09.681 --> 39:12.418
Is that you, buddy?

39:16.822 --> 39:18.758
Is anyone there?

39:21.893 --> 39:23.829
I swear to God...

39:25.063 --> 39:26.863
We're not messing around
in here.

39:26.865 --> 39:29.532
Did you hear that?

39:29.534 --> 39:31.704
We got guns.

40:31.831 --> 40:33.932
Shh!

42:14.233 --> 42:17.036
They're in the basement.

45:30.228 --> 45:31.096
Ray?

45:33.699 --> 45:35.168
Ray?

45:37.402 --> 45:38.870
Ray!

45:55.019 --> 45:58.287
- Kenneth!
- Where's Ray?

45:58.289 --> 46:00.159
The light!

46:01.226 --> 46:02.894
- Olivia!
- Ray!

47:00.452 --> 47:02.288
Don't!

47:13.931 --> 47:16.532
What was that?

47:16.534 --> 47:18.336
The attic hatch.

47:49.934 --> 47:52.404
- Keys!
- Ray!

47:53.572 --> 47:55.907
Arlene!

47:58.242 --> 47:59.943
Ray!

47:59.945 --> 48:01.978
Come on!

48:01.980 --> 48:03.213
Fuck!

48:03.215 --> 48:05.315
All right, Ray,
where's the ammo?

48:05.317 --> 48:08.153
No, no ammo! Go!

48:40.853 --> 48:43.322
Hey! Hey!

48:44.556 --> 48:46.555
Yeah.

48:46.557 --> 48:48.960
Help us!

48:52.597 --> 48:54.396
Hey! No, no, no...

48:54.398 --> 48:56.566
Hey! Hey!

48:56.568 --> 48:58.001
Hey, help us!

48:58.003 --> 49:00.972
Oh, come on! Come on!

49:02.641 --> 49:05.344
Chickenshits!

49:06.545 --> 49:09.014
They took Maisie,
didn't they?

49:21.425 --> 49:24.059
They turned around
and went the other way.

49:24.061 --> 49:26.097
You were running at them
with an axe.

49:42.581 --> 49:44.083
Mom...

49:45.217 --> 49:47.052
The stars are moving...

52:24.141 --> 52:26.745
Billy, do you want
to put that thing down?

52:40.324 --> 52:43.258
We received a phone call
not an hour ago.

52:43.260 --> 52:45.695
The call came from your place.

52:45.697 --> 52:48.363
Denise said that she believed
the woman she spoke to

52:48.365 --> 52:50.402
was you asking for me.

52:51.402 --> 52:53.570
Then the call got cut off
by the storm.

52:53.572 --> 52:56.472
Mind telling me
what that was about?

52:56.474 --> 52:58.575
I'm also hoping it'll explain
why the three of you

52:58.577 --> 53:00.642
are out in both the middle
of the night and nowhere

53:00.644 --> 53:03.345
looking like hell...
with an axe.

53:03.347 --> 53:06.249
Some people terrorized us.

53:06.251 --> 53:08.217
They invaded our home
and, uh...

53:08.219 --> 53:12.655
Ray, his brother Morgan,
my sister Arlene

53:12.657 --> 53:14.593
and Kenneth.

53:15.559 --> 53:17.327
- They're missing.
- Kenneth?

53:17.329 --> 53:19.295
As in Deputy Sheriff Burroughs?

53:19.297 --> 53:22.164
And our dog.

53:22.166 --> 53:23.733
Missing?

53:23.735 --> 53:26.336
They were taken.

53:26.338 --> 53:29.542
How many perps?
What are we dealing with here?

53:30.809 --> 53:32.675
We don't know.

53:32.677 --> 53:34.844
- We never saw them.
- A group.

53:34.846 --> 53:37.380
A small group.
Maybe three.

53:37.382 --> 53:38.751
Uh, three or four.

53:43.822 --> 53:45.557
OK.
Jump in.

54:06.811 --> 54:08.811
OK, folks.
Stay here.

54:08.813 --> 54:10.583
We'll go check it out.

55:29.594 --> 55:31.597
Power's still out.

55:32.831 --> 55:35.467
Which means they're still here.

56:38.463 --> 56:40.966
Well, whoever was here
ain't anymore.

56:46.670 --> 56:49.875
It doesn't look like
they were robbed neither.

56:52.911 --> 56:55.912
We should check the fuse box,
get the power back up.

56:55.914 --> 56:58.450
The storm, most likely.

57:03.722 --> 57:06.625
Five shots were fired
in the hall.

57:41.525 --> 57:43.061
Huh!

57:44.963 --> 57:48.834
It just all seems a little vague
for my liking.

57:55.005 --> 57:57.940
Well, they don't need
the attention.

57:57.942 --> 58:00.679
Specially not today.

58:06.518 --> 58:09.788
Something definitely
happened here tonight.

58:10.889 --> 58:14.023
We just need to get
to the bottom of it,

58:14.025 --> 58:17.894
but before any of that's
even remotely possible,

58:17.896 --> 58:19.998
I need to get me
a damn strong coffee.

58:29.106 --> 58:31.974
It certainly is bizarre.

58:31.976 --> 58:35.077
It's incredibly hard to imagine
that four adults...

58:35.079 --> 58:37.079
...and a dog!

58:37.081 --> 58:38.981
...four adults and a dog

58:38.983 --> 58:41.954
simply vanished
in the course of an hour.

58:43.153 --> 58:46.088
Look...

58:46.090 --> 58:51.059
The fact is, neither one of you
actually saw the perps.

58:51.061 --> 58:52.961
I'm telling you what happened.

58:52.963 --> 58:56.132
And I believe you, Olivia.
I really do. Every word.

58:56.134 --> 58:59.068
But my job is to make sense
of this situation,

58:59.070 --> 59:03.108
and this is a hard one to grasp.
Please understand that.

59:15.052 --> 59:17.887
We insist you come back
to the station with us.

59:17.889 --> 59:20.057
You can get some rest there
and some food.

59:22.092 --> 59:23.258
I'm staying.

59:23.260 --> 59:26.164
- Me too.
- We're not going anywhere.

59:30.902 --> 59:35.104
OK. Well, uh... We'll be back
in an hour with some officials

59:35.106 --> 59:38.039
who'll be able to actually
do something about this.

59:38.041 --> 59:39.809
In the meantime,

59:39.811 --> 59:41.744
I suggest you get some rest.

59:41.746 --> 59:43.079
I'll be parked outside on watch

59:43.081 --> 59:45.014
after I take the Sheriff
to the station, OK?

59:45.016 --> 59:48.854
If anything happens, anything
at all, you go straight to him.

59:57.061 --> 59:58.961
Olivia, I'm concerned.

59:58.963 --> 01:00:02.164
If any of this gets out,
any of it,

01:00:02.166 --> 01:00:06.068
it may have a hugely negative
effect on Maisie's case.

01:00:06.070 --> 01:00:08.006
What case?

01:00:10.108 --> 01:00:14.010
Look, I don't think this is what
people can know about right now,

01:00:14.012 --> 01:00:16.979
not for you
or your family's sake.

01:00:16.981 --> 01:00:19.715
Not the lights in the sky,
the disappearances,

01:00:19.717 --> 01:00:22.885
Ray, your sister, nothing.

01:00:22.887 --> 01:00:24.686
I'm going to keep it quiet,

01:00:24.688 --> 01:00:26.958
and I highly recommend
you do the same.

01:00:28.726 --> 01:00:29.994
Please.

01:00:33.864 --> 01:00:35.998
We'll figure this out.

01:00:36.000 --> 01:00:37.802
OK?

01:00:40.070 --> 01:00:41.806
Now get some rest.

01:01:47.204 --> 01:01:51.139
Now, is it just me
or is it one of those mornings?

01:01:51.141 --> 01:01:53.978
I've never had
a morning like this.

01:02:07.291 --> 01:02:09.057
I don't wanna ask, Doyle.

01:02:09.059 --> 01:02:11.827
Power failure, crop vandalism,
lights in the sky,

01:02:11.829 --> 01:02:13.329
phone's been ringing
off the hook.

01:02:13.331 --> 01:02:15.063
Madness of the crowds.

01:02:15.065 --> 01:02:18.971
Well, as a matter of fact, I'd
like to make a report myself.

01:02:23.173 --> 01:02:26.878
Contain everyone.
Get them all inside.

01:02:28.278 --> 01:02:31.083
What the hell's going on?

01:02:32.784 --> 01:02:34.251
Lights.

01:02:35.152 --> 01:02:37.720
In the sky. Uh...

01:02:37.722 --> 01:02:39.688
Fast.

01:02:39.690 --> 01:02:42.191
Non-ballistic.

01:02:42.193 --> 01:02:46.195
And then there was
this uh... other light.

01:02:46.197 --> 01:02:50.836
It was, uh... It was different.
It was bright.

01:02:51.802 --> 01:02:53.304
Within that light, I uh...

01:02:56.239 --> 01:02:58.142
I... I saw...

01:02:59.210 --> 01:03:00.912
Who?

01:03:02.246 --> 01:03:04.282
Who did you see?

01:03:08.452 --> 01:03:10.889
Maisie Anderson.

01:04:51.422 --> 01:04:53.889
Hey, boy.

01:04:53.891 --> 01:04:56.191
Oh, my God, Genghis! Hey!

01:04:56.193 --> 01:04:58.130
How have you been?

01:05:05.536 --> 01:05:10.039
Good boy! Good boy! Mm!

01:05:10.041 --> 01:05:13.976
Are the others here, huh?
Did you find the others?

01:05:13.978 --> 01:05:16.014
Huh?

01:05:31.896 --> 01:05:33.498
They're still here.

01:10:01.332 --> 01:10:03.264
'Ray, ready?

01:10:03.266 --> 01:10:05.235
'Go!'

01:10:12.176 --> 01:10:13.541
- 'Hey!'
- 'Hey!'

01:10:13.543 --> 01:10:15.544
'What do you have planned
for this evening?'

01:10:15.546 --> 01:10:16.745
'I don't know.'

01:10:16.747 --> 01:10:18.679
'You have
the house to yourself.'

01:10:18.681 --> 01:10:20.682
'I might watch TV.'

01:10:20.684 --> 01:10:23.451
'Let me take a look
at that picture.

01:10:23.453 --> 01:10:25.521
'Is that supposed to be me?'

01:10:25.523 --> 01:10:27.522
- 'Yeah.'
- 'Oh.

01:10:27.524 --> 01:10:29.191
'I look kinda ugly.

01:10:29.193 --> 01:10:31.660
'Is that how you portray
your old man?

01:10:31.662 --> 01:10:33.661
'Make me look like a bear?'

01:10:33.663 --> 01:10:36.568
'We're leaving now, Maisie.
Love you.'

01:10:42.206 --> 01:10:44.205
'Are my keys downstairs?'

01:10:44.207 --> 01:10:47.276
- 'Yep!'
- 'All right.

01:10:47.278 --> 01:10:48.744
'Love you, too, sweetheart!

01:10:48.746 --> 01:10:52.283
'Won't be long,
just a couple of hours!

01:10:54.284 --> 01:10:56.250
- 'She does not care.'
- 'She's not listening.'

01:10:56.252 --> 01:10:58.786
'No. She's like,
"Leave! Get out!"'

01:10:58.788 --> 01:11:00.488
'Is she writing?'

01:11:00.490 --> 01:11:03.825
'Yeah. And she's
really involved.'

01:11:03.827 --> 01:11:06.597
- 'Did you read it?'
- 'No.'

01:11:40.730 --> 01:11:42.766
Maisie!

01:11:43.900 --> 01:11:45.836
Maisie!

01:11:46.737 --> 01:11:48.806
Maisie!

01:12:03.020 --> 01:12:04.753
No, Maisie!

01:12:04.755 --> 01:12:06.821
Maisie! Maisie, stop!

01:12:06.823 --> 01:12:10.794
Don't answer the door!
Don't answer the door, Maisie!

01:13:42.519 --> 01:13:44.889
- 'How are you?'
- 'Good.'

01:14:05.943 --> 01:14:08.744
Hey, Genghis,
howya' doing, fella?

01:14:08.746 --> 01:14:10.745
- Hey!
- Want a lemonade?

01:14:10.747 --> 01:14:12.880
Uh, no thanks.
I'm still on duty.

01:14:12.882 --> 01:14:14.849
Just came by
to see how you all are.

01:14:14.851 --> 01:14:17.753
Mom and Dad have gone into town.
They'll be a couple of hours.

01:14:17.755 --> 01:14:19.388
Oh.
Oh, that's fine.

01:14:19.390 --> 01:14:21.022
You can wait here for them
if you like.

01:14:21.024 --> 01:14:22.960
They won't be long.

01:14:27.765 --> 01:14:29.630
Noah's staying at Parker's!

01:14:29.632 --> 01:14:31.566
Is Parker a friend?

01:14:31.568 --> 01:14:33.835
Yeah, from school!

01:14:33.837 --> 01:14:35.073
Right.

01:14:37.173 --> 01:14:39.174
- How's Aunt Arlene?
- Uh...

01:14:39.176 --> 01:14:40.878
She's good.

01:14:41.979 --> 01:14:43.815
She says hi.

01:14:55.458 --> 01:14:57.961
You never said you were here.

01:16:07.564 --> 01:16:09.967
What are you doing?

01:21:00.791 --> 01:21:02.025
Mom?

01:23:41.984 --> 01:23:44.451
Who are you?

01:23:50.961 --> 01:23:54.365
Let go of me!

01:24:22.091 --> 01:24:24.494
Where is she?

01:27:06.823 --> 01:27:08.388
'Kenneth!'

01:27:08.390 --> 01:27:10.460
No, no, no, no...

01:29:17.686 --> 01:29:19.689
'In my mind...

01:29:21.056 --> 01:29:23.924
'they must have known
of her existence

01:29:23.926 --> 01:29:26.294
'and visited her.

01:29:26.296 --> 01:29:27.794
'Then she disappeared.

01:29:27.796 --> 01:29:31.968
'I guess they must have,
uhm... waited.

01:29:34.770 --> 01:29:38.938
'waited for us to, uh,
figure it out for ourselves

01:29:38.940 --> 01:29:41.644
'before they intervened.'

01:29:44.346 --> 01:29:46.617
'To help us.

01:29:51.621 --> 01:29:53.890
'To show us.'

01:29:59.095 --> 01:30:01.597
'But honestly, we, uh...

01:30:02.664 --> 01:30:04.667
'We don't know.

01:30:05.868 --> 01:30:08.772
'I'm guessing
we'll never truly know.'

01:30:24.886 --> 01:30:27.990
'And now
I can put Maisie to rest.

01:30:32.127 --> 01:30:36.565
'Thanks to these... visitors.

01:30:38.967 --> 01:30:41.938
'These angels.'

